#### Reproduction


https://stackblitz.com/github/keatkeat87/angular-material-textarea-autosize-display-none-issue

Steps to reproduce:
![autosize-display-none-issue](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8691013/91519500-61acd580-e925-11ea-9593-207e458a56a1.gif)


#### Expected Behavior
What behavior were you expecting to see?
textarea size should display all text

#### Actual Behavior
What behavior did you actually see?
textarea size not display all text


Detail: 
this happens when ancestor use display none + change detect set to "OnPush"
when i check material source code, i found that, auto size only work when DoCheck.
so if textarea is not first child layer, it won't update the size.
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8691013/91519970-b13fd100-e926-11ea-8186-facaa56e0c15.png)


