Hi,

I'm trying to create a custom popup as per this [example](https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/javascript/examples/overlay-popup). In my component I initialize the popup and set the map:
```ts
this.popup = new Popup(
    new google.maps.LatLng(this.markerPosition),
    document.getElementById("content")
 );

this.popup.setMap(this.map.googleMap);
```

The popup displays on the map however, it's always fixed to the center and not at the coordinates supplied. If I pan the map the popup snaps back to the center every time. I have to admit that my CSS skills are almost non-existent (which might be the issue) but after searching for days I decided to ask for help here. Kindly assist if you can. Thanks
